    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/212</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1230</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing my No. 1183, of July 2, 1918, I
                    have the honor to forward herewith a, statement showing the dates, amounts, and
                        <pb facs="0768" n="656" xml:id="pg_656"/> character of the specie taken from
                    the Banco de Londres y México by the Mexican Government from January 17, 1917,
                    to and including May 24, 1918.<note n="1" xml:id="d604fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    This statement is identical with enclosure 5, of my confidential despatch No.
                    427, of August 22, 1917,<note n="1" xml:id="d604fn2">Not printed.</note> except
                    that the present enclosure shows dates, amounts, and character of specie which
                    has been taken from the bank since August 15, 1917. It will be observed that the
                    total amounts taken from the Banco de Londres y México to May 24, 1918, total
                    pesos 17,526,376.31.</p>
                <p>Additional information will be forwarded as soon as it shall have been
                    received.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P. Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
